# My Portfolio Website

A complete, responsive personal portfolio website built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Perfect for showcasing your skills, projects, and contact info.

## Features
- Responsive design (works on desktop and mobile)
- Dark mode toggle
- Contact form with JavaScript validation
- Smooth scrolling navigation
- Sections: Hero, About, Skills, Projects, Blog, Testimonials, Contact

## How to Use
1. Download or copy the files: `index.html`, `style.css`, `script.js`, and `README.md`.
2. Add your own `profile.jpg` image (or any image) to the root folder.
3. Customize content in `index.html` (e.g., change text, links, and projects).
4. Upload to GitHub:
   - Create a new repo (e.g., `my-portfolio`).
   - Upload all files.
   - Go to Settings > Pages > Deploy from branch > Select `main` > Save.
   - Your site will be live at `https://yourusername.github.io/my-portfolio`.

## Customization Tips
- Change colors in `style.css` (e.g., update `#007bff` to your favorite color).
- Add more projects or blog posts by copying HTML blocks.
- For real email sending, integrate a service like Formspree or Netlify Forms.

If you need help, feel free to ask!
